 Plan / worktree.yml / task.md are SHA-256 protected around the fix spawn; tampering → `REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=fix_tampered`. The fix protected set also includes the current pass's escalations/errors/fix-success/fix-guardrail files plus `reviews/suppressed.md`, so a fix agent cannot clear or flip the no-fix suppression list. If the fix agent exits with raw provider-limit `limit_text`, or a legacy AgentLimit wire-format error message, the runner writes `REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=limits_reached retry_after=<iso8601>` through the same `mark_review_phase_failure` helper used by triage; ordinary fix-agent errors still write `reason=fix_failed`.
 
+Claude/tmux fix agents launched through `Hive::ClaudeLauncher` now distinguish Stop-hook-signaled completion (`signaled=true`) from inferred completion (`signaled=false completion_reason=idle_prompt_no_sentinel`). On an inferred completion, Phase 4 accepts the result only when post-fix evidence is present: the worktree is dirty and will be auto-committed, `HEAD` advanced during the fix, or the clean/no-new-commit result carries explicit no-change evidence in the agent's final message. Accepted inferred completions emit `claude_completion_fallback` in `events.jsonl` with `level=warn`, `phase=fix`, `pass`, `sentinel`, `reason`, `session`, `evidence`, and `slug`, then continue through the existing auto-commit, fix guardrail, and `fix-success-NN.md` path. A clean/no-commit inferred completion without no-change evidence writes `REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=fix_incomplete_no_signal`; true timeouts and crashes still write `fix_failed`. See [[modules/events]].
+
